data.value:
Use this tool to extract elevation data from HEC-RAS geometry files (e.g. <HEC_RAS file name>.g01, etc.)
The tool will create X, Y, Z files that containing geo-referenced elevation data: • File 1: <HEC-RAS file name>_ALL_STATIONS.EXP has all elevation points. • File 2: <HEC-RAS file name>_CHANNEL_STATIONS.EXP has only the elevation points between the left and right bank stations. • File 3: <HEC-RAS file name>_ALL_POLY.EXP contains polygons that include all points for each reach. • File 4: <HEC-RAS file name>_CHANNEL_POLY.EXP contains convex polygons that include points between left and right banks for each reach.
These files can then be imported in Argus ONE or SMS to complement bed elevation data.
